RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALBAYAADER (IRE) stalked the pace from inside, steadied behind the leader at the three-eighths pole, tipped out and bid two wide around the turn, took over at the eight pole and drove clear. JERUSALEMA (IRE) chased on the inside into the turn, roused leaving the bend and entered the lane two wide, failed to find the needed response and flattened in the final furlong. K P HARRY KITTY dropped back off the pace, brushed REAL FIRE early, trailed into the turn, saved ground around the bend and was not a factor. MACHO QUEEN was off a bit slow from outside, bobbled crossing the dirt, traveled two to three wide around the bend and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAIZA bumped SWEET TROUBLE leaving the gate, showed speed inside a pair of rivals then chased around the clubhouse turn, switched outside the leaders on the backstretch, bid three then two wide on the far turn, gained command in upper stretch, disposed of SWEET TROUBLE in midstretch, challenged by PRIDE OF NILE late and held gamely. PRIDE OF THE NILE tracked three then two wide early, chased outside a rival into the far turn, angled over to the rail around the bend then asked two wide into the lane, angled out in upper stretch, drew alongside FAIZA late but could not get by. JUSTIQUE unhurried in the beginning and lagged behind in the three path on the clubhouse turn, took closer order up the backstretch outside rival, rounded the far turn four then three wide and got up for third. SWEET TROUBLE bumped with FAIZA and bobbled at the start, showed speed between rivals in the two path into the first turn, cleared and moved to the rail around the bend, pressured early on the backstretch before inching ahead again, challenged by FAIZA on the far turn, lost command in upper stretch and weakened in the furlong grounds. UNCONTROLLABLE tucked inside and settled off the pace, tipped three wide near the five-sixteenths pole, moved out further in the lane but failed to rally. BROADWAY GIRLS had good early speed outside a pair of rivals then stalked the leader in the two path, applied some pressure early on the backstretch then chased SWEET TROUBLE to the far turn, dropped back around that bend and tired in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHOCKING GREY was off a bit slow and lost his path in the beginning, trailed two wide early then outside a rival, moved to the inside for the far turn, gained along the rail, steered out in upper stretch and drove past the top pair late in the final sixteenth. ELEUTHERA vied between rivals early then pressed from outside, headed rival at the five-sixteenths pole, dueled into the stretch, took over outside the eighth pole, led into deep stretch but got outkicked by the winner. SUNSHINE BABE steered to the inside and settled early, suffered a mild shuffle early on the far turn, chased two wide then between rivals, angled out in the stretch and put in late run for the show honors. TRUE PATRIOT got bumped between rivals early, took a stalking position near the fence, continued inside then moved to the two path on the far turn, steered out four wide in upper stretch and finished willingly. ISSA COURT broke awkwardly then bumped with TRUE PATRIO shortly after, vied inside a pair of rivals then took control and set the pace under pressure from ELEUTHERA, was headed by that rival at the five-sixteenths pole, dueled to upper stretch, lost command near the eighth pole and faltered in deep stretch. PRECIOUS BABY broke inward, vied three deep then ceded command on the first turn, was keen early stalking outside the top pair, started to weaken under coaxing on the far turn and faded in the lane. LADY MARYANN stalked three wide early then got floated out to the five path around the clubhouse turn, got bothered early on the backstretch, remained wide on the far turn and came four wide into the stretch and had little left for the drive. IRISH WAHINE drifted four wide around the first turn, stalked off the rail in hand, dropped back on the far turn and angled to the inside and came up empty.

SWEET HELLO bumped with NOBE early and checked when losing her path, bid four deep around the bend, fought with inner pair to upper stretch, could not kick on with the winner in the furlong grounds but outfinished STORM D'ORO for the place honors. RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEWGRANGE stalked three wide into the first turn, prompted the pace three deep in the middle stages, lost some ground on the far turn and chased the top pair three wide into the lane, responded to the left hand and rallied three deep into the final sixteenth and dug in to prove best late. HOPPER was off a bit slow then sped to the front along the rail, set the pace inside PARNELLI AND NEWGRANGE up the backstretch, maintained command through the far turn, resisted into the final sixteenth but was overtaken by NEWGRANGE late. PARNELLI rated in the two path early then pressed between rivals, pestered HOPPER through the far turn and into the stretch, fought gamely into deep stretch but lacked the needed late punch. MESSIER chased four in the four path early, remained wide and traveled four deep on the second turn and finished evenly in the final furlong for a minor award. TRIPOLI stalked the speed from inside, cut the corner into the stretch and failed to offer the needed response. AMERICAN ADMIRAL was off slow to start, steadied between rivals early, trailed two wide then moved closer between rivals, entered the lane two wide and could not rally. BREAKFAST RIDE tracked from the three path early, raced outside a rival at the back into the far turn, entered the lane five wide and also lacked a rally. RACE.FOOTNOTES: KITTY KITANA (GB) stalked along the rail inside a rival, roused leaving the far turn, tipped out at the top of the stretch, closed well under right handed urging, drew alongside HONEY JAR past the sixteenth pole and drove clear near the wire. HONEY JAR sprinted clear and moved inside, opened up on the clubhouse turn, padded the lead in the middle stages, remained well clear into the final furlong, held a diminishing lead with a sixteenth to go and was run down by the winner. ANNAGHLASA (IRE) was closest in pursuit near the inside through both turns, came off the rail in the stretch and put in a mild late bid to whittle the gap late. CONTROL FUNCTION broke a bit slow, bumped and steadied between rivals early, sat off the pace on the inside, cut the corner into the stretch, asked right handed in the lane and offered a mild response to outkick AGREETODISAGREE for fourth. AGREETODISAGREE bumped with IMPLOSION in the beginning, raced three wide near the back early on, three deep into the far turn, advanced four wide around the bend and failed to threaten in the final furlong. MYFAVORITEDAUGHTER saved ground to the stretch and improved position. IMPLOSION tossed his head and bumped leaving the gate, tracked in the two path and weakened in the drive. POP POP'S DREAM raced between rivals at the back early on, traveled two wide on the second bend, swung out into the lane and failed to menace. HARDLY MISCHIEVOUS bumped with inner rival and steadied briefly early, traveled two in the two path then angled four wide into the stretch and was not a factor. KARAKATSIE settled inside, moved out and went two wide into the far turn, lacked room at the quarter pole, gained a clear path in the stretch but had little left to offer.
